article.headline: St. Bonaventure 71, Northern Illinois 62
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas (AP) -- Anthony Maestranzi scored 16 points, including three second-half 3-pointers, to lead Northern Illinois to a 71-62 come-from-behind victory over St. Bonaventure on Tuesday in the Flint Hills Islander Invitational. St. Bonaventure took a 28-27 lead into halftime, and the Bonnies led 48-41 with just under 11 minutes remaining in the game. But Maestranzi's 3-pointer with 10 minutes left gave Northern Illinois (4-4) all the momentum. Cory Sims made back-to-back layups to even the score at 48-48, and the Huskies sealed the victory by scoring 11 unanswered points. Maestranzi made all four of his free throws and four of his five 3-point shots. Ahmad Smith scored 22 points and had six rebounds and five assists for St. Bonaventure (0-10). Patrick Lottin added 12 points.
